The paper discusses the combination of machine learning and logic-based expert systems, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of RNN-based iterative neural networks for reasoning suggests that the paper may also fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), natural language processing (cs.CL), and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper's focus on symbolic logic and logical reasoning suggests that it may also fall under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO).
